Globally Focused Birmingham Investment Adviser, Cook & Bynum Capital Management, Launches New Mutual Fund | Business Wire
























































Globally Focused Birmingham Investment Adviser, Cook & Bynum Capital 
      Management, Launches New Mutual Fund






January 19, 2010 02:00 PM Eastern Standard Time



BIRMINGHAM, Ala.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Cook & Bynum Capital Management, LLC (“CBCM”) has announced the launch 
      of The Cook & Bynum Fund (“Fund”), a value-oriented mutual fund which 
      trades under the symbol COBYX. The Cook & Bynum Fund is CBCM’s first 
      publicly traded fund. Following many years of successful private 
      investment management experience, CBCM created the fund as a result of 
      demand for a mutual fund product from its growing client base.1 
      The Cook & Bynum investment philosophy is centered on the belief that 
      superior, long-term results are achieved through investing as owners 
      purchasing high quality companies at a significant discount to their 
      true economic value.
    

      The Cook & Bynum Fund is an open-end, non-diversified, value-oriented 
      mutual fund that seeks long term growth of capital. The Fund focuses on 
      making long-term, concentrated equity investments in both domestic and 
      foreign companies while minimizing the risk of permanent capital loss. 
      With this new fund CBCM continues its tradition of investing alongside 
      its investors in order to promote fund manager accountability.
    

      When discussing Cook & Bynum’s approach to investing, co-portfolio 
      manager Richard P. Cook explains, “In order to maximize our long term 
      results, we try to identify businesses around the world whose futures we 
      can reasonably predict. So that we may confidently do so, these 
      businesses must be within our circle of competence. They must have a 
      durable competitive advantage to allow them to predictably earn money in 
      the future, and they must also be run by people we would like to have as 
      partners. When these three elements are in place, we buy businesses that 
      are available at a substantial discount to our valuation. Hopefully, 
      that discount will provide outsized returns when we are correct and a 
      ‘margin of safety’ when we are not.”
    

      J. Dowe Bynum, co-portfolio manager of the Cook & Bynum Fund, continues, 
      “We seek partners who understand our investment philosophy and our 
      long-term approach. These characteristics in our partners are critical 
      to our mutual success. We attempt to align our interests with our 
      partners by investing substantially all of our investable net worth 
      alongside them. We do not invest outside the funds we manage.”
    

The Cook & Bynum Fund Facts



        The Fund is co-managed by Richard P. Cook and J. Dowe Bynum.
      

        The Fund’s expense ratio is 1.88%2, and there are no loads 
        or 12b-1 fees.
      

        The Fund imposes a 2% redemption fee if shares are redeemed within 60 
        days of purchase in order to discourage market timing and short-term 
        trading.
      

        The minimum regular account size is $5,000.
      

        The minimum IRA account size is $1,000.
      

        The Fund commenced operations on July 1, 2009.
      


About Cook & Bynum Capital Management, LLC


      Cook & Bynum Capital Management, LLC is a federally registered 
      investment adviser located in Birmingham, Alabama that manages over $100 
      million in assets as of December 31, 2009. CBCM was founded in 2001 by 
      Birmingham natives Richard P. Cook and J. Dowe Bynum. In addition to 
      managing the Cook & Bynum Fund, CBCM manages money for private clients.
    

About Fund Management


Richard P. Cook*


      Mr. Richard P. Cook is co-portfolio manager and President of the Fund. 
      Before forming Cook & Bynum Capital Management in 2001, Mr. Cook worked 
      for Tudor Investment Corporation in Greenwich, Connecticut. Mr. Cook 
      attended Hampden-Sydney College where he graduated in three years summa 
      cum laude with a B.S. in Economics, Mathematics, & Applied Mathematics 
      and was a member of Phi Beta Kappa.
    

J. Dowe Bynum*


      Mr. J. Dowe Bynum is co-portfolio manager and Vice President and 
      Secretary of the Fund. Before forming Cook & Bynum Capital Management in 
      2001, Mr. Bynum worked as an analyst in the Equities Division of 
      Goldman, Sachs & Co., Inc. in New York, New York. Mr. Bynum attended 
      Princeton University and graduated with a B.S.E. in Operations Research 
      & Financial Engineering and a Certificate in Finance.
    

      For questions regarding this press release, contact Ashley Buha* at Cook 
      & Bynum Capital Management at ashley@cookandbynum.com 
      or (205) 994-6652.
    

An investor should consider investment objectives, risks, charges and 
      expenses carefully before investing. To obtain a prospectus, which 
      contains this and other information, visit www.cookandbynum.com
or call 1-877-839-COBY. Read the prospectus carefully before 
      investing.


The Cook & Bynum Fund is new and has limited operating history.


The Cook & Bynum Fund invests in securities using a value approach to 
      investing. Value-based investments are subject to the risk that the 
      broad market may not recognize their intrinsic values. The Cook & Bynum 
      Fund is a non-diversified mutual fund, which means that the Fund invests 
      in a smaller number of securities when compared to more diversified 
      funds. This strategy exposes the Fund and its shareholders to greater 
      risk of loss from adverse developments affecting portfolio companies.


There are risks associated with foreign investing including political 
      and economic instability, fluctuations in currency and exchange rates, 
      and an increased risk of price volatility associated with less 
      uniformity in accounting and reporting requirements. Investing in 
      emerging markets accentuates these risks.


The Cook & Bynum Fund is distributed by ALPS Distributors, Inc.


